<ul><li><b>Power stations</b> generate alternating current at 50Hz and 25kV.</li><li><b>Step-up transformers</b>&nbsp;at the power station increase the alternating voltage to 400kV for long-distance transmission via the grid system.<br></li><li><b>Step-down transformers</b>&nbsp;operate in stages, home are supplied with single-phase AC at 230V.<br></li></ul>